e unofficial award for the most steezy rider, after pulling t-bogs on one of the double jumps lap after lap.\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the unofficial award\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1526}, {\"ngram\": \"the most steezy rider\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"t-bogs\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"the double jumps\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"lap\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"lap\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after 25 minutes of racing Pidcock attacked uphill by the switchbacks, with only Viktor Koretsky of France able to follow.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9927673758718502, \"rank\": 0.004530458483080368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"25 minutes\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"the switchbacks\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"only Viktor Koretsky\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alan Hatherly of South Africa stayed close behind.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}, {\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.95811838541843, \"rank\": 0.02618891118019723, \"text\": \"South Af